367_130732_000015_000002 This is the recipe for eight people, and it is well worth trying if you are giving a dinner of importance:
367_130732_000016_000000 Bisque of Crawfish
367_130732_000017_000000 Take thirty crawfish, from which remove the gut containing the gall in the following manner: Take firm hold of the crawfish with the left hand so as to avoid being pinched by its claws; with the thumb and forefinger of the right hand pinch the extreme end of the central fin of the tail, and, with a sudden jerk, the gut will be withdrawn.
367_130732_000018_000001 Put these ingredients into a stewpan and fry them ten minutes, then throw in the crawfish and pour on them half a bottle of French white wine.
367_130732_000018_000002 Allow this to boil and then add a quart of strong consomme and let all continue boiling for half an hour.
367_130732_000018_000003 Pick out the crawfish and strain the broth through a napkin by pressure into a basin in order to extract all the essence from the vegetables.
367_130732_000019_000001 Reserve some of the spawn, also half of the body shells with which to make the crawfish butter to finish the soup.
367_130732_000019_000002 This butter is made as follows: Place the shells on a baking sheet in the oven to dry; let the shells cool and then pound them in a mortar with a little lobster coral and four ounces of fresh butter, thoroughly bruising the whole together so as to make a fine paste.
367_130732_000019_000003 Put this in a stewpan and set it over a slow fire to simmer for about five minutes, then rub it through a sieve with considerable pressure into a basin containing ice water.
367_130732_000020_000000 Reverting to the original recipe: Take the remainder of the crawfish and add thereto three anchovies, washed for the purpose, and also the crusts of French rolls, fried to a light brown color in butter.
367_130732_000020_000001 Pound all these thoroughly together and then put them into a stewpan with the broth that has been reserved in a basin, and having warmed the bisque thus prepared rub it through a sieve into a fine puree.
367_130732_000020_000002 Put this puree into a soup pot and finish by incorporating therewith the crawfish butter and season with a little cayenne pepper and the juice of half a lemon.
367_130732_000020_000003 Pour the bisque quite hot into the tureen in which have been placed the crawfish tails, and send to the table.
