4350_10919_000002_000000 At the end of the winter, in the Shtcherbatskys' house, a consultation was being held, which was to pronounce on the state of Kitty's health and the measures to be taken to restore her failing strength.
4350_10919_000002_000001 She had been ill, and as spring came on she grew worse.
4350_10919_000002_000002 The family doctor gave her cod liver oil, then iron, then nitrate of silver, but as the first and the second and the third were alike in doing no good, and as his advice when spring came was to go abroad, a celebrated physician was called in.
4350_10919_000002_000003 The celebrated physician, a very handsome man, still youngish, asked to examine the patient.
4350_10919_000003_000002 The prince frowned and coughed, listening to the doctor.
4350_10919_000003_000004 "Conceited blockhead!" he thought, as he listened to the celebrated doctor's chatter about his daughter's symptoms.
4350_10919_000003_000005 The doctor was meantime with difficulty restraining the expression of his contempt for this old gentleman, and with difficulty condescending to the level of his intelligence.
4350_10919_000003_000006 He perceived that it was no good talking to the old man, and that the principal person in the house was the mother.
4350_10919_000003_000007 Before her he decided to scatter his pearls.
4350_10919_000003_000009 The prince withdrew, trying not to show how ridiculous he thought the whole performance.
4350_10919_000003_000010 The princess was distracted, and did not know what to do.
4350_10919_000003_000011 She felt she had sinned against Kitty.
4350_10919_000004_000000 "Well, doctor, decide our fate," said the princess.
4350_10919_000004_000001 "Tell me everything."
