8131_117017_000005_000001 O'Neill had turned to run, and then seemed to think better of it.
8131_117017_000005_000002 His hand darted down to his belt, just as Gordon reached him.
8131_117017_000006_000000 The heavy locust stick met the man's wrist before the weapon was half drawn-another gun!
8131_117017_000006_000001 Guns suddenly seemed to be flourishing everywhere. The gun dropped from O'Neill's hand as the wrist snapped, and the Stonewall chief let out a high pitched cry of pain.
8131_117017_000006_000002 Then another cop came around a corner at a run.
8131_117017_000007_000000 "You can't do it to me!
8131_117017_000007_000001 I'm reformed; I'm going straight!
8131_117017_000007_000002 You damned cops can't...." O'Neill was blubbering.
8131_117017_000008_000000 The other cop had yanked out O'Neill's wallet, and now tossed it to Gordon.
8131_117017_000008_000002 The cops had been passing them on the hope of finding one of the leaders.
8131_117017_000009_000000 Some turned away as Gordon and the other cop went to work, but most of them weren't squeamish.
8131_117017_000009_000001 When it was over, the two picked up their whimpering captive.
